From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Rurix Godot Bridge <rurix@example.invalid>
Date: Mon, 13 Jul 2026 09:00:00 +0800
Subject: [PATCH] Add default-disabled GRX Route B rd_native tonemap in-frame
 compute replacement

Stacked on 0001..0029 (the branch-HEAD gpu_culling tip). This is the first
non-scaffold REAL replacement pass: Route B drives the Rurix tonemap kernel as
a first-class in-frame RenderingDevice compute pass instead of the out-of-frame
rxgd shim bridge, and when it records, the native Godot tonemapper is genuinely
skipped (no scaffold clear, unlike patch 0013).

- drivers/d3d12/d3d12_hooks.h: new default-false virtual
  try_record_tonemap_rd_native(RID source, RID dest, Size2i src_size,
  Size2i dest_size, float exposure, float white, float luminance_multiplier).
  It takes Godot RID handles (not native ID3D12Resource* handles like the
  shim-path try_record_tonemap) so the module can build an RD uniform set and
  compute pipeline directly. Adds core/templates/rid.h + core/math/vector2i.h
  includes for the RID / Size2i parameter types. Base returns false, so hooks
  that do not override it (or the absence of a hooks singleton) keep the native
  Godot tonemap path.
- modules/rurix_accel/register_types.cpp: two new default-safe settings,
  independent of the four existing tonemap shim settings (which are untouched):
  rendering/rurix_accel/passes/tonemap/backend (int, default 0; 0=disabled /
  1=shim / 2=rd_native) and rendering/rurix_accel/passes/tonemap/rd_container_path
  (string, default ""). Defaults keep the RD-native path disabled.
- modules/rurix_accel/rurix_accel.{h,cpp}: try_record_tonemap_rd_native
  override. Lazily builds the compute pipeline once (FileAccess reads the Rurix
  container -> shader_create_from_bytecode -> compute_pipeline_create, latching
  rd_native_tonemap_load_failed on any failure so it is not retried per frame),
  runs a usage-bits preflight (source SAMPLING_BIT, dest STORAGE_BIT), binds
  t0=source (SRV/UNIFORM_TYPE_TEXTURE) and u0=dest (UAV/UNIFORM_TYPE_IMAGE) via
  UniformSetCacheRD (auto-invalidated on resize), packs the 28-byte b0 push
  constants ([i64 source_width, i64 source_height, f32 exposure, f32 white,
  f32 luminance_multiplier]), and dispatches ceil(dest/8) groups with
  compute_list_* on the main RenderingDevice. The draw graph's ResourceTracker
  inserts the barriers; there is no submit()/sync() (a local-RD-only concept).
  The one-shot RXGD_RD_NATIVE_TONEMAP active marker is emitted via print_verbose
  when the pipeline is first built (not per-frame).
- servers/rendering/renderer_rd/renderer_scene_render_rd.cpp: in the tonemap
  can_use_storage leg, backend == 2 runs the rd_native gate BEFORE the shim
  gate; a successful record skips both the shim gate and the native tonemapper.
  backend != 2 leaves the pre-existing shim/native chain byte-for-byte unchanged.

Fail-closed everywhere: with the default backend == 0 (and empty container
path), rd_native is never engaged and the native Godot tonemapper renders. The
kernel covers only the LINEAR tonemapper with the SDR convert_to_srgb leg (no
auto exposure, glow, FXAA, BCS, color correction, debanding, or other tonemap
modes), so the candidate scene must use tonemap_mode LINEAR to align with the
kernel subset. RXGD_ABI_VERSION is unchanged (this path does not touch the C
ABI struct layout and sets no RxGdCaps.flags bit; rd_native is bridge-
independent). No performance claim is made.
